              {
                "type": "input",
                "subType": "alert",
                "header": "",
                "content": {
                  "aws": "Amazon ECR offers three options for encryption of images– SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, DSSE-KMS. By default, Amazon ECR uses server-side encryption with Amazon S3-managed encryption keys (SSE-S3). This is offered at no additional charge. <br>For SSE-KMS, you pay AWS KMS charges to generate or retrieve the data key used for encryption and decryption. For pricing on AWS KMS, visit the <a href='https://aws.amazon.com/kms/pricing/'>AWS KMS pricing Page</a>. <br>For DSSE-KMS, in addition to the charges for AWS KMS mentioned above, you pay an additional per gigabyte encryption fee for the second layer of encryption and decryption of data.",
                  "aws-iso": "Amazon ECR offers three options for encryption of images– SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, DSSE-KMS. By default, Amazon ECR uses server-side encryption with Amazon S3-managed encryption keys (SSE-S3). This is offered at no additional charge. <br>For SSE-KMS, you pay AWS KMS charges to generate or retrieve the data key used for encryption and decryption. <br>For DSSE-KMS, in addition to the charges for AWS KMS mentioned above, you pay an additional per gigabyte encryption fee for the second layer of encryption and decryption of data.",
                  "aws-iso-b": "Amazon ECR offers three options for encryption of images– SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, DSSE-KMS. By default, Amazon ECR uses server-side encryption with Amazon S3-managed encryption keys (SSE-S3). This is offered at no additional charge. <br>For SSE-KMS, you pay AWS KMS charges to generate or retrieve the data key used for encryption and decryption. <br>For DSSE-KMS, in addition to the charges for AWS KMS mentioned above, you pay an additional per gigabyte encryption fee for the second layer of encryption and decryption of data.",
                  "aws-cn": "Amazon ECR offers three options for encryption of images– SSE-S3, SSE-KMS, DSSE-KMS. By default, Amazon ECR uses server-side encryption with Amazon S3-managed encryption keys (SSE-S3). This is offered at no additional charge. <br>For SSE-KMS, you pay Amazon KMS charges to generate or retrieve the data key used for encryption and decryption. For pricing on AWS KMS, visit the <a href='https://www.amazonaws.cn/en/kms/pricing/'>Amazon KMS pricing Page</a>. <br>For DSSE-KMS, in addition to the charges for Amazon KMS mentioned above, you pay an additional per gigabyte encryption fee for the second layer of encryption and decryption of data."
                },
                "alertType": "info",
                "partitions": [
